==Italian==
===Noun===
'''metrò''' ''m or f'' (''see usage notes'')

#(''short form of'' '''[[metropolitana]]''') [[subway]] (''US''), [[underground]] (''UK''), [[Tube]] (''the London underground'')

====Usage notes====
*The gender can be either masculine or feminine, depending on whether '''metrò''' is considered as being a [[calque]] from French ''[[métro]]'', which is masculine, or a short form of '''metropolitana''', which is feminine.